Subject&#58; Re&#58; how can I contact sysadmin of ra.srce.hr?
Date-Sent&#58; Monday, August 30, 2010 2&#58;28 PM -0500

Hello

First apologies due to slow response -- I was on travel.

Yes this project had been actively discussed a while ago. Security team
and Marco made couple surveys with the site admins. At the time, the
level of annoyance was not high enough to get OSG devote resources on
this. So it was pushed onto the back burner.

At that time, I asked Keith if he would like to experiment in FermiGrid
and set up a centrally available CRL repository. His plan at the time
was to test it internally at fermilab and then if agreed upon, make it
available to CMS sites. Gradually it may be made available to all OSG
sites.

I just spoke with Steve Timm this morning and found out the latest on
this effort. Keith had already setup a working test server.
Unfortunately , FermiGrid will not have the resources to move the test
CRL service into production until the end of November.

If the annoyance level is high enough, I am willing to bring this up
with GOC.

how should we proceed from here?

I can send another  email to osg-int and ask anyone who feels strongly
about this to reply. The resources in OSG are scarce that unless site
admins strongly state this as a necessity, this will not get done. With
<div id='show_1772142587' class=''><button class="btn">Show More</button></div><div class='detail hidden' id='detail_1772142587'>the emails, I can go back to GOC once more.

any other ideas to proceed?

...Mine
