Hi Mine,
I raised a probably similar problem with Igor at the site administrators meeting.
I received complains from a couple of site administrators in ATLAS (MWT2, BNL) that
the machine that they use to update certificates and CRLs seems to get banned. This
happens at least with one CA. The CA is not responsive to requests from the sites.
They say that everything works fine (and it does from hosts that are not banned).
I can get more detail if needed.

I was asked if OSG could bring back and deploy the centralized solutions for CA/CRLs
discussed at the time of the all hands meeting, we had a survey about it.

Best,
Marco

